network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":46,"dimensions":47},"Deep and well carved, with a U-shaped cut letters of generally regular height. Most letters are c.75mm tall; O is consistently smaller than the other letters (55-60 mm), S taller at 95 mm, and the numeral 50 is 110 mm. A deep round interpunct is viisble at the end of line 3.",[48,56,61,66,72],{"type":49,"l":50,"from":51,"to":51,"h":52,"unit":53,"atLeast":54,"atMost":55},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","75-95","mm","75","95",{"type":49,"l":57,"from":58,"to":58,"h":59,"unit":53,"atLeast":60,"atMost":55},"Line 2","line2","55-95","55",{"type":49,"l":62,"from":63,"to":63,"h":64,"unit":53,"atLeast":65,"atMost":54},"Line 3","line3","60-75","60",{"type":49,"l":67,"from":68,"to":68,"h":69,"unit":53,"atLeast":70,"atMost":71},"Line 4","line4","70-110","70","110",{"type":73,"l":74,"from":51,"to":58,"unit":53},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2",{"_":76,"notBefore":77,"notAfter":78},"252-248 BCE",-252,-248,[80],{"_":8,"type":81,"ref":82,"region":83},"modern","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462323","Sicilia",[85],[86,87],37.7905564,13.3101399,[89,90],37.8054867,13.3542511,"Sicily",{"_":4,"role":3,"ref":5},{"_":94,"mainLang":95,"languages":96},"Latin","la",[94],"175816",{"n":99,"url":100,"height":101,"width":102,"desc":103,"surfaceType":104},"screen","ISic000610_tiled.tif","5520px","3680px","Photo J. Prag, 2023.10.28, courtesy Museo Civico di Corleone.","front",[106,109,111,113],{"atLeast":107,"atMost":108},75,95,{"atLeast":110,"atMost":108},55,{"atLeast":112,"atMost":107},60,{"atLeast":114,"atMost":115},70,110,[117,117,118,119,120,121,122,123,124,125],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Degrassi, 1965, ILLRP","Di Vita, 1955, Un milliarium del 252 a.C. e l'antica via Agrigento-Panormo","Degrassi, 1962, Nuovi miliari arcaici","Di Vita, 1963, Il miliario siciliano del console C. Aurelio Cotta","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the arch